#. <section class="sutta" id="sn2.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Nānātitthiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Various Sectarians"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Khemasutta"
msgstr "22. With Khema"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.22:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho khemo devaputto bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Standing to one side, the god Khema recited these verses in the Buddha’s "
"presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.1"
msgid "“Caranti bālā dummedhā,"
msgstr "“Foolish and unintelligent people"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.2"
msgid "amitteneva attanā;"
msgstr "treat themselves like an enemy."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.3"
msgid "Karontā pāpakaṃ kammaṃ,"
msgstr "They do bad deeds"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.4"
msgid "yaṃ hoti kaṭukapphalaṃ."
msgstr "with bitter fruit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.1"
msgid "Na taṃ kammaṃ kataṃ sādhu,"
msgstr "It’s not good to do a deed"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.2"
msgid "yaṃ katvā anutappati;"
msgstr "after doing which you’re tormented by regrets;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.3"
msgid "Yassa assumukho rodaṃ,"
msgstr "you experience the result"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.4"
msgid "vipākaṃ paṭisevati."
msgstr "weeping, with a tearful face."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.132"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.1"
msgid "Tañca kammaṃ kataṃ sādhu,"
msgstr "It’s good to do a deed"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.2"
msgid "yaṃ katvā nānutappati;"
msgstr "after doing which you’re free of regrets;"

# I don’t understand the word patita: can it really be derived from pacceti?
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.3"
msgid "Yassa patīto sumano,"
msgstr "you experience the result"

# See BB on finishing the deva’s verses here.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.4"
msgid "vipākaṃ paṭisevati."
msgstr "joyful, with a happy mind.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: Paṭikacceva → paṭigacceva (bj)
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.1"
msgid "Paṭikacceva taṃ kayirā,"
msgstr "“As a precaution, you should do"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.2"
msgid "yaṃ jaññā hitamattano;"
msgstr "what you know is for your own welfare."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.3"
msgid "Na sākaṭikacintāya,"
msgstr "A thinker, a wise one would not proceed"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.4"
msgid "mantā dhīro parakkame."
msgstr "thinking like the cart driver."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: maṭṭhaṃ → panthaṃ (bj, pts1-2) | pasatthaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.1"
msgid "Yathā sākaṭiko maṭṭhaṃ,"
msgstr "Suppose a cart driver leaves the highway,"

# reading maṭṭha above.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.2"
msgid "samaṃ hitvā mahāpathaṃ;"
msgstr "so even and well compacted."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.3"
msgid "Visamaṃ maggamāruyha,"
msgstr "They enter upon a rough road,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.4"
msgid "akkhacchinnova jhāyati."
msgstr "and fret when their axle breaks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ dhammā apakkamma,"
msgstr "So too, an idiot departs the good"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.2"
msgid "adhammamanuvattiya;"
msgstr "to follow what’s against the good."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.3"
msgid "Mando maccumukhaṃ patto,"
msgstr "Fallen in the jaws of death,"

# See BB’s comments on the commentarial readings for this line. I f ind it odd, surely there should be a vairation to apply the metaphor properly. In the parallel in Mil for this, the readings are the same. But note that the parallels in Chinese and Skt omit the cart metaphor.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.4"
msgid "akkhacchinnova jhāyatī”ti."
msgstr "they fret like their axle’s broken.”"
